{
  "stem": "4361.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, they had two ghettos in Sighet.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was the big ghetto and the small ghetto.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My mother and I, and my sister-in-law, Rose, and her two babies [SIGHS] were in the big ghetto.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my brother, my older brother and his wife and his child who was about a year and a half old-- a little boy, Andicka-- they lived in another part of the town closer to the Jewish section.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So around that part, they set-- they set up-- the Hungarians-- set up a second ghetto, which was called the small ghetto",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we couldn't even get in touch with them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They wouldn't-- my brother couldn't even come to be with us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father was incarcerated, and now we are in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You were in the big ghetto, or the little--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the big ghetto.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm often asked, because I speak now and then, how did you live?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What did you-- how could you buy food?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, were there barbed wires?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No, there were not barbed wires, but what the Hungarians did-- and you have to understand that this was all done under the supervision and with the direction and under the control of the Nazis.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we still did not see any Nazis except the two German officers who where billeted in our house, who would leave in the morning and come back in the evening.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I'm sure that they were in the municipal building and-- and-- and writing out the orders and planning what was happening now.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were billeted in a small house in the big ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And well, first of all, clearly we had money.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
